iN","target":"recdMHFSmu222VnJG","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recRvkLcMPoWt2wiN","target":"recg9ZkB8FoyQTH8v","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"recV6lQnSZ2vIkxGD","ref":"Heb.11.1","text":"Now faith is the substance of things hoped for, the evidence of things not seen.","year":64},{"id":"rec2J9vGxsY1VgYUA","ref":"Heb.11.2","text":"For by it the elders obtained a good report.","year":64},{"id":"recMO0pFqTthGvVBM","ref":"Heb.11.3","text":"Through faith we understand that the worlds were framed by the word of God, so that things which are seen were not made of things which do appear.","year":64},{"id":"recTqBCczSTqN2zxT","ref":"Heb.11.4","text":"By faith Abel offered unto God a more excellent sacrifice than Cain, by which he obtained witness that he was righteous, God testifying of his gifts: and by it he being dead yet speaketh.","year":64},{"id":"recP1XH3RZb8Tzhkp","ref":"Heb.11.5","text":"By faith Enoch was translated that he should not see death; and was not found, because God had translated him: for before his translation he had this testimony, that he pleased God.","year":64},{"id":"recexzi7znaInkrZu","ref":"Heb.11.6","text":"But without faith it is impossible to please him: for he that cometh to God must believe that he is, and that he is a rewarder of them that diligently seek him.","year":64},{"id":"recSOFbS3XfOm0s7s","ref":"Heb.11.7","text":"By faith Noah, being warned of God of things not seen as yet, moved with fear, prepared an ark to the saving of his house; by the which he condemned the world, and became heir of the righteousness which is by faith.","year":64},{"id":"recmkXk4YsOuXCWct","ref":"Heb.11.8","text":"By faith Abraham, when he was called to go out into a place which he should after receive for an inheritance, obeyed; and he went out, not knowing whither he went.","year":64}]}
